arn.description: ARN of this auto scaling configuration version.

autoScalingConfigurationName.description: Name of the auto scaling configuration.

autoScalingConfigurationRevision.description: The revision of this auto scaling configuration.

latest.description: Whether the auto scaling configuration has the highest `auto_scaling_configuration_revision` among all configurations that share the same `auto_scaling_configuration_name`.

maxConcurrency.description: Maximal number of concurrent requests that you want an instance to process. When the number of concurrent requests goes over this limit, App Runner scales up your service.

maxSize.description: Maximal number of instances that App Runner provisions for your service.

minSize.description: Minimal number of instances that App Runner provisions for your service.

status.description: Current state of the auto scaling configuration. An INACTIVE configuration revision has been deleted and can't be used. It is permanently removed some time after deletion.

tags.description: Key-value map of resource tags. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: Map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
